1
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:11,900
<i>- Bye!
- Deja vu.</i>

2
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:12,900
<i> This is how you two started,</i>

3
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:13,900
<i>- isn't it?
- What?</i>

4
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:14,900
<i> Did the car just die?</i>

5
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:15,900
<i> You got any signal?</i>

6
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:17,233
<i> No. Zero bars.</i>

7
00:00:17,367 --> 00:00:18,433
<i>- Come on.
- Hello? Anybody there?</i>

8
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:19,900
<i> Marj, you're wet.</i>

9
00:00:20,033 --> 00:00:20,967
<i>I think you're about
to give birth.</i>

10
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:22,700
<i> It's not my due date yet.</i>

11
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,000
<i> The baby's in distress.</i>

12
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:25,133
<i> We need to operate now.</i>

13
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:26,333
<i> Where's Paolo?</i>

14
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:27,833
<i>- Where's Pao?
- I already called them.</i>

15
00:00:27,967 --> 00:00:29,700
<i>They're not answering,
but I sent a message.</i>

16
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,767
<i> Where's Paolo?</i>

17
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,700
<i> I want to see my baby.</i>

18
00:00:34,867 --> 00:00:36,000
<i>She's alive, but she's
in critical condition.</i>

19
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:38,067
<i>The next 24 hours
are very important.</i>

20
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:39,633
<i>What we did was just
a moment of temptation.</i>

21
00:00:39,767 --> 00:00:40,967
<i>And it can't ever happen again.</i>

22
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:42,000
<i> You enjoyed it, didn't you?</i>

23
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:43,300
<i> So why don't we keep going?</i>

24
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:44,633
<i> No one's going to find out.</i>

25
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:46,500
<i>What happened in this house
stays in this house.</i>

26
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:47,333
<i> You understand?</i>

27
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:48,167
<i> What are you guys doing?</i>

28
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:48,933
<i> Where are you?</i>

29
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:50,300
<i> Marj just gave birth.</i>

30
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:52,333
<i>If there's anyone to blame here,
it's me.</i>

31
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:54,833
<i>I feel like this is karma
for what I did.</i>

32
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:56,000
<i> What did you do?</i>

33
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:01,133
Wait.

34
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,000
Are you blaming yourself

35
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:06,033
because of your history
of womanizing?

36
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:12,467
Paolo, stop blaming yourself.

37
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:16,300
Didn't you leave that life
behind a long time ago?

38
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:18,833
You've changed, right?

39
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:20,300
You don't do that anymore.

40
00:01:22,433 --> 00:01:23,267
Yes.

41
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:26,500
So don't blame yourself, okay?

42
00:01:28,233 --> 00:01:29,567
Don't think that way.

43
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:31,733
It's okay.

44
00:02:36,933 --> 00:02:37,700
Let's talk.

45
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:43,333
Edward, it's been
such a long day.

46
00:02:44,167 --> 00:02:46,600
Can't we just talk
about this at home?

47
00:02:54,467 --> 00:02:55,500
Why couldn't I reach you?

48
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,900
Didn't Paolo
already tell you?

49
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:04,400
The car broke down
in the middle of the rain.

50
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:07,067
We had no signal.

51
00:03:08,767 --> 00:03:10,100
I was exhausted.

52
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:14,067
I just wanted to go home
because I'm tired.

53
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,133
Why is it so hard for you
to believe me?

54
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:18,867
Okay.

55
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:20,367
I'm sorry.

56
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:23,200
I was just worried about you.

57
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:27,100
Just say it.

58
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:32,233
You don't trust me.

59
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,100
No, no, no.

60
00:03:38,167 --> 00:03:39,300
Of course, I trust you.

61
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:41,500
I just...

62
00:03:42,733 --> 00:03:43,833
I just don't trust Paolo.

63
00:03:46,733 --> 00:03:47,967
Come on, let's go home.

64
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:50,867
Let's say goodbye.

65
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,133
Sorry you got dragged into this.

66
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,100
I'm sorry.

67
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:18,533
Hi, Marj.

68
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,233
<i>- Hi, Thea.
- How are you?</i>

69
00:04:23,367 --> 00:04:25,167
I brought you some fruits.

70
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:26,700
And a little gift.

71
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:27,933
It's nothing fancy.

72
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:29,500
Wow, thank you.

73
00:04:32,267 --> 00:04:33,600
I didn't even get to hug you
last night

74
00:04:33,733 --> 00:04:36,000
because Paolo wouldn't leave
your side.

75
00:04:37,733 --> 00:04:38,833
Yeah because he felt guilty.

76
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:45,233
That he wasn't here
when I had surgery,

77
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:47,233
and when they took the baby out.

78
00:04:50,133 --> 00:04:52,467
Your husband is so rich,

79
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,233
but he still won't
replace his car.

80
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:55,933
Look what happened.
It broke down on us.

81
00:04:57,367 --> 00:04:58,733
Yeah, he told me.

82
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,600
Thank you for not leaving
my husband.

83
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:06,667
Oh, please,
I should be thanking him.

84
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:11,500
He didn't leave me until Edward
finally got in touch with us.

85
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,667
You know, he was like Superman.

86
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,267
He looked like
he was about to fly off

87
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:17,700
and leave me at the repair shop
just to get here faster.

88
00:05:20,567 --> 00:05:22,033
Hey, don't get too excited now.

89
00:05:22,167 --> 00:05:24,700
You're laughing so hard at me.

90
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:30,233
But at least
you're laughing now.

91
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,900
Not like last night.

92
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:34,500
You were devastated.

93
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,067
I'm so sad, Thea.

94
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,200
It's so hard.

95
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:44,300
They still won't let me
see my baby.

96
00:05:45,367 --> 00:05:47,433
The doctor said
she'll be okay.

97
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,933
But I'm still scared.

98
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:55,133
I mean, aren't babies supposed
to be handed to their moms

99
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:56,267
right after they're born?

100
00:05:57,933 --> 00:05:59,833
You know, I saw something once.

101
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:01,500
A baby who wasn't breathing.

102
00:06:02,233 --> 00:06:04,967
Then they put him
on his mom's chest...

103
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,200
and suddenly he got better.

104
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:09,833
Like his mom's hug healed him.

105
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:16,200
I just want to hold my baby.

106
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,500
Maybe she'll get better.

107
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:21,433
Maybe she'll breathe normally.

108
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:24,767
I just want to hold her
so badly.

109
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,500
Don't be sad.

110
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,267
It's okay.

111
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,667
At least you're safe.

112
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,633
Your baby's safe.

113
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:49,967
Thank you.

114
00:06:58,033 --> 00:06:58,867
Love?

115
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:01,000
<i> Love.</i>

116
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:04,400
<i> Sorry.</i>

117
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:08,200
I'm getting emotional again.

118
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,167
I was just telling Thea a story.

119
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,000
She brought me a gift.

120
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,333
You probably think I was
telling her something sad?

121
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,900
Why would I do that?

122
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:34,133
Marj's already vulnerable.

123
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,867
What do you think you're doing?

124
00:07:56,033 --> 00:07:56,933
What?

125
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:00,167
I'm just comforting my friend.

126
00:08:01,133 --> 00:08:02,600
She obviously needs it.

127
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:06,733
I'm just being a great friend
to Marj.

128
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:08,067
Don't you want that?

129
00:08:12,433 --> 00:08:13,400
Wait.

130
00:08:14,133 --> 00:08:17,100
Why are you acting
so paranoid, Paolo?

131
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,933
Are you scared your wife's
going to find out...

132
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,967
you're no different from her ex?

133
00:08:30,767 --> 00:08:33,000
That you're just like her dad?

134
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:37,233
Isn't that what she hates?

135
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:41,333
I'm not like those men.

136
00:08:45,667 --> 00:08:47,167
You're too late, Pao.

137
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:49,467
You already are.

138
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:53,800
You already hurt Marj.

139
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,267
She just doesn't know it yet.

140
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:58,200
She doesn't need to know.

141
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:02,033
Let's not ruin both our lives.

142
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,300
We both made a mistake.

143
00:09:05,933 --> 00:09:07,433
And we need to move on.

144
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:10,500
Really?

145
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,067
Is that what you really need?

146
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:17,933
You know what?

147
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:20,467
You're right.

148
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,700
What I really need
is peace of mind.

149
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:25,800
So forget whatever
happened between us.

150
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:29,300
And can you please
just stay away from us?

151
00:09:29,467 --> 00:09:30,633
Especially from Marj.

152
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:32,400
We already have enough problems.

153
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:34,100
Don't add to them.

154
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:39,100
What are you two arguing about?

155
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:52,767
No. No, we're not arguing.

156
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,333
One of our clients,

157
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:59,067
the one we were supposed to meet
yesterday, called Paolo.

158
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:02,200
He's upset
because we couldn't make it.

159
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,600
So I told Paolo not to even
worry about that client.

160
00:10:06,733 --> 00:10:08,967
Marj's more important, right?

161
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:11,533
Right, Pao?

162
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:13,767
Yeah, she's right.

163
00:10:17,967 --> 00:10:18,667
Let's go, Hon.

164
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,567
I've still got a meeting
with some potential investors.

165
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,300
Bro.

166
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,067
Edward.

167
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,033
I haven't thanked you yet.

168
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:38,000
Thank you for bringing
Marj here right away.

169
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:39,933
I owe you one.

170
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,600
I just did what was right.

171
00:10:44,900 --> 00:10:45,767
For Marj.

172
00:10:49,367 --> 00:10:50,233
Let's go, Hon.

173
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:56,700
Oscar, please load the bags
into the car, okay?

174
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:57,567
Yes, Sir.

175
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:58,200
I'll wait for you
at the entrance.

176
00:10:58,333 --> 00:10:59,133
- Okay.
- Ma'am.

177
00:11:00,967 --> 00:11:02,000
Come on.

178
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:10,767
There's our baby.

179
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:18,467
Easy...

180
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:31,333
Baby...

181
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:35,600
Your daddy and I are heading
home for now, okay?

182
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:39,500
Just get stronger.

183
00:11:39,633 --> 00:11:41,000
We'll be right back.

184
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:48,300
I'll visit you every day
until you're all better.

185
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:52,200
Keep fighting, Baby.

186
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:55,700
I love you.

187
00:11:58,900 --> 00:11:59,600
Love...

188
00:12:01,167 --> 00:12:02,733
should we name our baby?

189
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:09,267
How about Jasmine?

190
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:11,733
Jasmine?

191
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,867
It means a gift from God.

192
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,133
A gift from God.

193
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:25,833
I like it.

194
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:32,567
Get stronger, our Baby Jasmine.

195
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:37,467
We can't wait to play
with you...

196
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:39,700
kiss you...

197
00:12:41,533 --> 00:12:42,400
hug you.

198
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:46,100
We love you so much, Sweetheart.

199
00:12:50,733 --> 00:12:52,433
Get stronger, Baby.

200
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:56,867
We'll keep praying
that you grow stronger

201
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,867
so we can all finally
be together.

202
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:21,000
Why do you keep
canceling my calls?

203
00:13:30,067 --> 00:13:30,867
Hon?

204
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,933
Who's that?

205
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:34,967
Why are you still up?

206
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:38,167
It's nothing. A client.

207
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:40,333
I just messaged a client.

208
00:13:42,433 --> 00:13:43,367
At this hour?

209
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:50,533
You seriously need to stop
being such a workaholic.

210
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:52,367
Hey!

211
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:54,967
You're so silly.

212
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:11,867
Sorry.

213
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,267
- Why?
- Sorry, Hon.

214
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:14,367
Rain check tonight.

215
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,200
My lower stomach hurts.

216
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:19,100
I think I'm about
to get my period.

217
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:22,367
Sorry.

218
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,567
Hon...

219
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:24,767
Come on, please.

220
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,600
It's been a while.

221
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:29,567
And I've really missed you.

222
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,633
I promise,
I'll make it up to you.

223
00:14:35,767 --> 00:14:36,867
Just not tonight.

224
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,167
Okay.

225
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:45,133
Come on, let's go to sleep.

226
00:14:51,167 --> 00:14:53,733
<i>At least this keeps you busy,
right?</i>

227
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:56,067
It takes your mind off things.

228
00:14:56,767 --> 00:14:59,000
Everything's going to be okay.

229
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,633
<i> Yours looks so pretty.</i>

230
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:08,900
Mom.

231
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:11,433
How's Marj?

232
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,767
She still looks
devastated, right?

233
00:15:16,267 --> 00:15:17,033
Of course.

234
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:21,067
She still hasn't
even held her baby.

235
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:26,900
Hey.

236
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:29,867
Why are you looking at me
like that, Mom?

237
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:34,867
Edward, be honest with me.

238
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:38,067
Do you still have
feelings for Marj?

239
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:42,667
What kind of question
is that, Mom?

240
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:45,000
I already have Thea.

241
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:47,433
You didn't answer my question.

242
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,067
I'm just worried about
what happened to her.

243
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:54,133
Exactly.

244
00:15:54,267 --> 00:15:56,700
You're overly worried about her.

245
00:15:58,567 --> 00:16:00,067
Edward, you can't fool me.

246
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:05,800
Son, let Marj go.

247
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:09,100
She's your brother's wife now.

248
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:12,400
And you have a niece with them.

249
00:16:12,533 --> 00:16:14,233
Soon they'll be
a complete family.

250
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:19,367
Edward, let go of that love.

251
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:27,233
Just like a tree letting go
of its dead leaves.

252
00:16:28,367 --> 00:16:29,567
Not with bitterness,

253
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:32,100
but with peace
because it's time.

254
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,933
Why don't you just
focus on Thea?

255
00:16:39,367 --> 00:16:42,500
<i>You don't even realize
how lucky you are to have her.</i>

256
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:44,633
<i> Look at her.</i>

257
00:16:44,767 --> 00:16:46,600
<i>Even after everything
that happened</i>

258
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:48,233
<i> between her and Marjorie,</i>

259
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:50,500
she's still making an effort
to be friends again.

260
00:16:50,933 --> 00:16:52,367
Now they're like sisters.

261
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:56,000
Be content with her.

262
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:58,800
Don't let her go.

263
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:16,500
I pumped some breast milk
for my baby.

264
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:18,000
Please take care of it for me.

265
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:18,533
Yes, Ma'am.

266
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:19,567
I'll handle it.

267
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:35,567
Love, look.

268
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:38,300
It's like she knows we're here.

269
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:43,833
Of course.

270
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:49,000
I'm sure she's been
waiting for us.

271
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:56,967
Love?

272
00:17:57,833 --> 00:17:59,033
What's happening?

273
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:00,467
What's happening to Jasmine?

274
00:18:01,467 --> 00:18:02,800
- Nurse!
- Nurse!

275
00:18:02,933 --> 00:18:03,700
Nurse!

276
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:05,500
Nurse!

277
00:18:05,633 --> 00:18:07,100
Love, what's happening to her?

278
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,767
Wait, wait.
You can't go in there.

279
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:13,733
We have to stay here.

280
00:18:13,867 --> 00:18:15,167
What about Jasmine?

281
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,900
Nurse, what's going on? Nurse!

282
00:18:39,633 --> 00:18:40,867
What's happening?

283
00:18:42,267 --> 00:18:43,433
The nurse is there.

284
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:56,767
Nurse...

285
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:04,533
Nurse, what happened to my baby?

286
00:19:04,667 --> 00:19:07,000
We're sorry if we scared you.

287
00:19:07,133 --> 00:19:10,000
The sensor just got dislodged.

288
00:19:10,133 --> 00:19:12,000
It moved out of place
because the baby moved.

289
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:13,967
Oh my God.

290
00:19:14,100 --> 00:19:15,700
Is she safe? Is everything okay?

291
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,333
Is she okay? Is my baby safe?

292
00:19:17,467 --> 00:19:20,400
Yes, Sir. Baby Jasmine's vitals
are stable.

293
00:19:21,533 --> 00:19:23,367
Her recovery's steady.

294
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:26,067
In a few weeks, you'll be able
to take her home.

295
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,100
As long as the progress
continues.

296
00:19:28,633 --> 00:19:29,500
Excuse me.

297
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,867
Love, did you hear that?

298
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:43,700
We'll get to take
Baby Jasmine home.

299
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:49,633
Thank God He heard our prayers.

300
00:20:24,267 --> 00:20:26,967
Hey, Thea,
your coffee's getting cold.

301
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:30,400
It's Paolo.

302
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:32,300
He's avoiding me even at work.

303
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:34,467
He dropped all the projects

304
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,533
that we were supposed
to handle together

305
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:38,333
and assigned me
a different partner.

306
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:42,467
Maybe you're just
overthinking it.

307
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:45,267
He's a new dad.

308
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:47,567
Maybe he's on paternity leave.

309
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:50,367
Paternity leave?

310
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:53,633
He's at the office,
meeting clients.

311
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,767
No.

312
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,333
He's definitely avoiding me.

313
00:20:58,500 --> 00:20:59,967
Then stop hoping.

314
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:02,100
Besides, you've got Edward.

315
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:03,833
He's still a Torrecampo.

316
00:21:03,967 --> 00:21:07,700
Yes, but he's not
the golden boy.

317
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,933
Turns out he's not the favorite.

318
00:21:11,067 --> 00:21:14,733
He lied to me when he said
he was better than his brother.

319
00:21:14,867 --> 00:21:18,000
That he deserved to inherit
the family business more.

320
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:21,000
But when I had lunch
with his parents,

321
00:21:21,133 --> 00:21:25,000
that's when I found out what
his dad really thinks of Edward.

322
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,067
A loser.

323
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:29,033
Seriously?

324
00:21:29,167 --> 00:21:30,300
<i> Exactly.</i>

325
00:21:30,433 --> 00:21:33,800
That's why I'm so annoyed
because I met Paolo too late.

326
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:35,933
Right when he was already taken.

327
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:37,167
And the worst part?

328
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:40,867
He ended up with the one person
I hate the most.

329
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,267
So, I don't stand a chance
with him.

330
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:53,833
This smells kind of stale.

331
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:55,600
What? This is freshly brewed.

332
00:21:57,067 --> 00:21:58,500
Girl, are you okay?

333
00:21:59,833 --> 00:22:00,767
Friend!

334
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:02,433
Hold on, I'm just going
to use the restroom.

335
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:04,767
What's wrong with you?

336
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:10,200
The baby's here!

337
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:12,500
- Hi, Ma'am!
- She's so beautiful.

338
00:22:12,633 --> 00:22:17,733
She's such a cute baby girl.

339
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:22,100
Love, love, Baby.
Let me get that.

340
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,333
- She's beautiful, right?
- Hey!

341
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:28,200
- She looks like me!
- Oh my!

342
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:30,500
The baby's here!

343
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:32,000
Here she is.

344
00:22:32,133 --> 00:22:35,300
She's so beautiful.

345
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:38,133
<i> Marj!</i>

346
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:40,967
Can I hold the baby?

347
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,233
- Yolly?
- Yes, Ma'am?

348
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:45,367
Make sure the AC is on
in the nursery, okay?

349
00:22:45,667 --> 00:22:47,700
And you, help Yolly out

350
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:49,767
so the baby feels comfortable,
okay?

351
00:22:50,267 --> 00:22:53,533
Jobert, can you play
with her later?

352
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:05,467
Oh my!

353
00:23:06,633 --> 00:23:08,100
Grandfather's excited.

354
00:23:08,233 --> 00:23:11,667
Look at our Baby Jasmine.

355
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:16,033
She's so beautiful.

356
00:23:16,167 --> 00:23:17,567
One day,

357
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:20,233
she'll carry on my legacy.

358
00:23:20,367 --> 00:23:23,300
Hope you take after your dad?

359
00:23:23,467 --> 00:23:26,567
Be just like your daddy, Baby.

360
00:23:26,700 --> 00:23:28,167
Let me hold her.

361
00:23:29,433 --> 00:23:31,933
- Easy, easy.
- Of course.

362
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:35,167
Wow!

363
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:39,033
<i> Hello!</i>

364
00:23:41,667 --> 00:23:42,833
You okay?

365
00:23:47,367 --> 00:23:48,367
Yes, Love.

366
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,933
I'm just hoping that now
that Jasmine's finally here,

367
00:23:52,067 --> 00:23:53,600
everything will be okay.

368
00:23:53,733 --> 00:23:56,133
I hope nothing bad
ever happens again.

369
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:59,200
I won't let that happen again.

370
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:31,133
Congratulations.

371
00:24:31,267 --> 00:24:33,900
You're eight weeks pregnant,
Miss Villareal.

372
00:24:36,833 --> 00:24:39,367
Doc, are you sure?

373
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:41,267
Yes. You're pregnant.

374
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:45,000
I'll prescribe some pregnancy
supplements, okay?

375
00:24:45,133 --> 00:24:48,533
I'll just grab some sample
vitamins from the other clinic.

376
00:24:48,667 --> 00:24:50,700
I'll be back in five minutes.

377
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:02,500
Oh my God.

378
00:25:10,767 --> 00:25:12,167
Lalaine,

379
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:14,433
my gut was right.

380
00:25:14,567 --> 00:25:16,200
<i> Oh my gosh!</i>

381
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:17,500
<i> It's confirmed?</i>

382
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:20,033
<i>You and Edward
are having a baby?</i>

383
00:25:22,367 --> 00:25:24,367
This isn't Edward's baby.

384
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,500
<i> What?</i>

385
00:25:25,633 --> 00:25:27,167
<i> What do you mean?</i>

386
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:30,167
If I'm eight weeks pregnant...

387
00:25:30,933 --> 00:25:33,700
that lines up with when Paolo
and I got stranded together.

388
00:25:34,567 --> 00:25:37,300
And after that, Edward and I
never even slept together.

389
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:43,733
So I'm sure of it.

390
00:25:45,767 --> 00:25:47,900
This baby is Paolo's.

391
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:56,200
How are you?

392
00:25:56,333 --> 00:25:57,433
How are things with you
and Thea?

393
00:25:57,567 --> 00:25:58,500
Is something wrong?

394
00:25:58,633 --> 00:26:00,700
I don't know.
She's been acting differently.

395
00:26:00,833 --> 00:26:03,200
Why won't you answer
my messages?

396
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:04,333
I can't even get through to you.

397
00:26:04,467 --> 00:26:06,000
You can't just walk away
from me.

398
00:26:06,133 --> 00:26:07,833
Especially not now
that I'm pregnant,

399
00:26:07,967 --> 00:26:08,933
and you're the father.

400
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:11,667
When I first met you,
I was actually impressed.

401
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,200
I thought, for once,

402
00:26:13,333 --> 00:26:15,300
Edward finally did
something right.

403
00:26:15,433 --> 00:26:17,333
But you see,
I was wrong about you.

404
00:26:17,467 --> 00:26:19,667
You're just as materialistic
as the rest of them.

405
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:23,067
If being a good mother makes me
a bad person in your book,

406
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:24,167
then so be it.

407
00:26:24,300 --> 00:26:25,700
What were you thinking?

408
00:26:25,833 --> 00:26:28,100
It will ruin our family!

409
00:26:28,233 --> 00:26:29,600
What are you doing here?

410
00:26:29,733 --> 00:26:31,867
I just happen to be attending

411
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:34,467
a Torrecampo charity event
tonight.

412
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,200
That's where I'm exposing
everything

413
00:26:37,333 --> 00:26:39,000
that happened
between Paolo and me.

414
00:26:39,133 --> 00:26:41,367
Since he treats me like
I'm disgusting anyway, fine.

415
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:43,233
We're all going down together.

416
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:45,767
I was going to tell you anyway.

417
00:26:45,900 --> 00:26:47,000
The truth is...

418
00:26:47,133 --> 00:26:48,567
I'm pregnant.

419
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:49,833
And he's the father.

420
00:26:49,967 --> 00:26:55,333
I'll make sure his wife
and his whole family

421
00:26:55,467 --> 00:26:57,233
turn their backs on him.
